dcterms:description: Continuous Engine Operational Data (CEOD) collected at high frequencies during flights, consisting of several hundred parameters measured at a frequency of 1Hz, allowing for a complete digital representation of the operational history of an engine.
dcterms:title: Continuous Engine Operational Data (CEOD)

dcterms:description: Selected Exhaust Gas Temperature (DEG_C) is a specific parameter derived from the CEOD dataset, used as a target variable for modeling.
dcterms:title: Selected Exhaust Gas Temperature (DEG_C)

dcterms:description: Simulated data used in related work for modeling aircraft jet engine parameters, specifically for the take-off and cruising phases.
dcterms:title: Simulated Data (used in related work)

dcterms:description: Small scale jet engine data used in related work for predicting jet engine parameters for control design.
